EN: When people are in a tense state, they sometimes experience drowsiness and illusions.

ZH: 她在疲惫不堪时产生了一种错觉，好像自己在梦境中。
EN: She experienced an illusion of being in a dream when she was exhausted.

ZH: 这种药物可能引起幻觉和错觉。
EN: This medication may cause hallucinations and illusions.

ZH: 我常常感到冷，但实际上是自己的错觉。
EN: I often feel cold, but it is actually my own illusion.

ZH: 在迷雾中行走会产生视觉上的错觉。
EN: Walking in the fog can create visual illusions.

ZH: 当我饿得不行时，我会有一种错觉，好像所有的食物都在向我召唤。
EN: When I'm extremely hungry, I have an illusion that all food is calling out to me.

ZH: 焦虑症患者常常会有一种错觉，认为周围的人都在审视他们。
EN: Patients with anxiety disorders often have an illusion that people around them are scrutinizing them.

